# CareMetric Train -- production environment variables
#
# This app has no backend server of its own: the React SPA in
# artifacts/caremetric-train talks to Supabase directly via supabase-js, and
# Supabase Edge Functions (supabase/functions/*) handle anything that needs
# the service-role key or an outbound API call (user provisioning, CSV
# import, PDF generation, HeyGen video generation).
#
# Railway hosts and runs the app below. Set these as Railway service
# variables (Project -> Service -> Variables), NOT by committing a real
# .env file. See DEPLOYMENT.md for the full setup walkthrough.

# --- Supabase (browser-safe, required) ---------------------------------
# Vite only exposes env vars prefixed VITE_ to the client bundle. The anon
# key is safe to ship to the browser: it has no access beyond what Row
# Level Security grants an unauthenticated/authenticated request.
#
# BUILD-TIME: both values are baked into the JS bundle when `vite build`
# runs (the build fails loudly if they're missing). Changing them on the
# Railway service requires a redeploy (rebuild), not just a restart.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-or-publishable-key

# --- App runtime -----------------------------------------------------------
# Railway injects PORT automatically; only set it locally if you need a
# specific port. NODE_ENV is set by Railway's Railpack builder automatically
# too, so setting it yourself is optional/harmless.
# PORT=8080
# HOST is optional; server/index.mjs binds dual-stack "::" by default.
NODE_ENV=production

# APP_URL is not read by the app at runtime (the browser's own origin is
# used for Supabase Auth redirect links, see
# artifacts/caremetric-train/src/pages/auth/ForgotPassword.tsx).
# It's listed here as documentation of the production URL. Both origins the
# app is served from must be in Supabase Auth -> URL Configuration ->
# Redirect URLs: https://caremetrictrain.com/login and
# https://penntrain-production.up.railway.app/login
# APP_URL=https://caremetrictrain.com

# BASE_PATH is an optional, build-time-only override read by vite.config.ts
# (feeds Vite's `base` option, which the wouter router reads back via
# import.meta.env.BASE_URL). Only needed if the SPA is ever served from a
# non-root subpath; leave unset for a standard Railway root-domain deploy,
# where it correctly defaults to "/".
# BASE_PATH=/

# --- Explicitly NOT used by this app (do not add) --------------------------
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY   -- lives ONLY in Supabase Edge Function
#                                secrets (`supabase secrets set ...`), never
#                                in Railway or any client-reachable process.
#                                Guardrail: server/index.mjs and every file
#                                under src/ must never reference this name.
# DATABASE_URL                -- no direct Postgres access from app code;
#                                everything goes through supabase-js + RLS.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL/ANON_KEY -- this is a Vite app, not Next.js.
# SESSION_SECRET / AUTH_SECRET -- auth/session state is Supabase Auth
#                                (GoTrue) via cookies/localStorage; the app
#                                has no server-side session of its own.
# NPM_CONFIG_PRODUCTION / RAILPACK_PRUNE_DEPS -- NEVER set these: every
#                                dependency of the app (including vite) is a
#                                devDependency, and either of these makes the
#                                install skip devDependencies, emptying the
#                                build. The buildCommand passes --prod=false
#                                as a guard, but don't fight it.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY           -- no billing integration exists in this repo.
# RESEND_API_KEY               -- no transactional email provider is wired
#                                in; password reset/invite emails are sent
#                                by Supabase Auth's built-in mailer.
# RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN        -- Railway sets this automatically for
#                                Railway-provided domains; the app doesn't
#                                need to read it (see note above re: browser
#                                origin), but it's useful when scripting
#                                your own deploy tooling.

# --- Supabase Edge Function secrets (set via `supabase secrets set`, NOT
#     here -- these run on Supabase's infrastructure, not Railway) ---------
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# HEYGEN_API_KEY=
